The Swiss foreign ministry supports LTTE's willingness to negotiate and calls for peace talks to resume promptly.
They advocate for a federal structure in a united Sri Lanka and endorse Norway's role as a facilitator.
The Tamil Tigers are preparing for peace talks in Switzerland, seeking aid to pressure the government.
Internal conflicts within the LTTE hinder peace negotiations, with accusations of collusion with the government.
Efforts to revive talks have been stalled since April, with hopes pinned on Japanese envoy Akashi's intervention.
The situation remains tense as both sides navigate a fragile ceasefire.
